      q: "Tropics Corp. reports revenue under the accrual basis of accounting. Selected information is shown below: Accounts receivable balance 12/31/Year 1 $ 475,000 Accounts receivable balance 12/31/Year 2 850,000 Collections from customers during Year 2 1,125,000 The collections bookkeeper does not record any amounts to accounts receivable, but records all collections as a credit to revenue using the cash basis of accounting. What amount is debited or credited to revenue as a correcting entry to convert the revenue from the cash basis to the accrual basis?",
      choices: ["$1,500,000 credit", "$1,500,000 debit", "$375,000 debit", "$375,000 credit"],
